CreateExclusionGroupRequest.description: Given a title entity token and exclusion group details, will create a new exclusion group for the title.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Name.description: Friendly name of the exclusion group.

example.Name: Commerce Exclusion Group
example.Description: Exclusion group for independent, commerce-related experiments

CreateExperimentRequest.description: Given a title entity token and experiment details, will create a new experiment for the title.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExclusionGroupTrafficAllocation.description: Percentage of exclusion group traffic that will see this experiment.

SegmentId.description: Id of the segment to which this experiment applies. Defaults to the 'All Players' segment.

TitlePlayerAccountTestIds.description: List of title player account IDs that automatically receive treatments in the experiment, but are not included when calculating experiment metrics.

Variants.description: List of variants for the experiment.

example.Name: BackgroundColor Experiment
example.Description: Tests whether a green background color increases revenue

ExperimentId.description: The ID of the new experiment.

DeleteExclusionGroupRequest.description: Given an entity token and an exclusion group ID this API deletes the exclusion group.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExclusionGroupId.description: The ID of the exclusion group to delete.

DeleteExperimentRequest.description: Given an entity token and an experiment ID this API deletes the experiment. A running experiment must be stopped before it can be deleted.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExperimentId.description: The ID of the experiment to delete.

TrafficAllocation.description: Percentage of exclusion group traffic that will see this experiment.

GetExclusionGroupsRequest.description: Given a title entity token will return the list of all exclusion groups for a title.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExclusionGroups.description: List of exclusion groups for the title.

GetExclusionGroupTrafficRequest.description: Given a title entity token and an exclusion group ID, will return the list of traffic allocations for the exclusion group.

ExclusionGroupId.description: The ID of the exclusion group.

GetExperimentsRequest.description: Given a title entity token will return the list of all experiments for a title, including scheduled, started, stopped or completed experiments.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Experiments.description: List of experiments for the title.

GetLatestScorecardRequest.description: Given a title entity token and experiment details, will return the latest available scorecard.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Scorecard.description: Scorecard for the experiment of the title.

GetTreatmentAssignmentRequest.description: Given a title player or a title entity token, returns the treatment variants and variables assigned to the entity across all running experiments

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The entity to perform this action on.

ConfidenceIntervalEnd.description: The upper bound of the confidence interval for the relative delta (Delta.RelativeValue).

ConfidenceIntervalStart.description: The lower bound of the confidence interval for the relative delta (Delta.RelativeValue).

DeltaAbsoluteChange.description: The absolute delta between TreatmentStats.Average and ControlStats.Average.

DeltaRelativeChange.description: The relative delta ratio between TreatmentStats.Average and ControlStats.Average.

InternalName.description: The machine name of the metric.

Movement.description: Indicates if a movement was detected on that metric.

Name.description: The readable name of the metric.

PMove.description: The expectation that a movement is real

PValue.description: The p-value resulting from the statistical test run for this metric

PValueThreshold.description: The threshold for observing sample ratio mismatch.

StatSigLevel.description: Indicates if the movement is statistically significant.

StdDev.description: Observed standard deviation value of the metric.

Value.description: Observed average value of the metric.

DateGenerated.description: Represents the date the scorecard was generated.

Duration.description: Represents the duration of scorecard analysis.

EventsProcessed.description: Represents the number of events processed for the generation of this scorecard

LatestJobStatus.description: Represents the latest compute job status.

SampleRatioMismatch.description: Represents the presence of a sample ratio mismatch in the scorecard data.

IsControl.description: Represents whether the variant is control or not.

MetricDataRows.description: Data of the analysis with the internal name of the metric as the key and an object of metric data as value.

PlayerCount.description: Represents the player count in the variant.

VariantName.description: Name of the variant of analysis.

StartExperimentRequest.description: Given a title entity token and an experiment ID, this API starts the experiment.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExperimentId.description: The ID of the experiment to start.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExperimentId.description: The ID of the experiment to stop.

UpdateExperimentRequest.description: Given a title entity token and experiment details, this API updates the experiment. If an experiment is already running, only the description and duration properties can be updated.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

ExclusionGroupTrafficAllocation.description: Percentage of exclusion group traffic that will see this experiment.

SegmentId.description: Id of the segment to which this experiment applies. Defaults to the 'All Players' segment.

TitlePlayerAccountTestIds.description: List of title player account IDs that automatically receive treatments in the experiment, but are not included when calculating experiment metrics.

Variants.description: List of variants for the experiment.

example.Description: Tests whether a green background color increases revenue

IsControl.description: Specifies if variant is control for experiment.

TitleDataOverrideLabel.description: Id of the TitleDataOverride to use with this variant.

TrafficPercentage.description: Percentage of target audience traffic that will see this variant.
